reviews.review: Mixed feelings. Lots of great elements, some legit emotion and on its own, it’s a fine movie. BUT heading in to this new trilogy, my only hard requirement was that it not take away from the OT. That req was not met. Adam Driver delivers a great performance and the film paid homage to our favorite Princess.
Thought the early scenes were rushed and it needed more time to build the story.

A fasted paced and exciting movie. The Rise of Skywalker ends the saga in great way. Deffinalty not perfect but its flaws are far out weighed by its exciting story. Its is worth the time to go and see!!!
Awesome! Great job patching TLJ disaster.
Definitely made up for the train wreck of a movie that The Last Jedi was.

I’m pretty sure the writers forgot that Finn wanted to tell Rey something, guess it didn’t really matter but kinda bugged me they never looped back to that.
The dialogue was atrocious, the story was very weak and you could see that they struggled to wrap everything up both for the trilogy and the story overall, the use of poorly developed new characters to draw out some sort of feelings from the audience was cheesy and just not well executed, the final act of the movie kinda saved what garbage wasn’t on fire already at that point but it still was not worth seeing.

Just flat out bad.

I think it did a fine job of salvaging the franchise and wrapping up an iconic saga. Far better than the previous two and I personally would rank it below the original trilogy and slightly better than Revenge of the Sith. Thanks to The Last Jedi, it basically had to convey a trilogy's worth of information in one movie all while paying homage to all of Star Wars in a grand finale, and JJ Abrams did his job. Cinematography, CGI, and soundtrack were incredible. The acting was fine. Loved that Rose was effectively nonexistent and that they left off developing Finn's useless character line which allowed audiences to connect more with the storyline of Rey and Ben Solo. Instead, we got a much-needed pair of bros in Finn and Poe to break the ice (though some of Poe's emotional lines were laughably bad). It was a good balance of Star Wars fun, storyline salvaging, and paying last respects to the franchise that has entertained millions for 30 years.

I thought this was a good way to end the Skywalker Saga. I can see where fans are upset ab this movie becuz it basically avoids some of the Last Jedi. Other than that great visuals, music, and amazing action. This movie is not boring! Get out and see it 2-3 times because you prob missed some things the first time.

As a lifelong Star Wars fan I was thoroughly pleased with Episode IX. There were some moments that I felt could have been done better, but all of that is overshadowed by the good. I laughed, I cheered, and I cried. Three times. All in all, this was good Star Wars.
